Costs of Rosneft’s Vankor Project Reach $34 Bln, Vedomosti Says

-- B y   H e n r y   M e y e r
-- 
2011-04-08T04:29:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/costs-of-rosneft-s-vankor-project-reach-34-bln-vedomosti-says.html
OAO Rosneft,  Russia ’s biggest oil
producer, will need to invest 960 billion rubles ($34 billion)
in its Vankor project in Siberia by 2037, Vedomosti reported,
citing an expert assessment prepared for the company.  This marks an increase from the previous projected costs of
754 billion rubles, the Moscow-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Henry Meyer in Moscow at 
